WEBVTT

00:31.753 --> 00:35.756
♪♪ [ Orchestra: Classical, Slow Tempo ]

00:47.518 --> 01:25.764
♪♪ [ Continues ]

02:15.773 --> 02:19.776
♪♪ [ Singing Opera In German ]

02:58.066 --> 03:36.895
♪♪ [ Singing Continues ]

04:27.280 --> 04:31.283
♪♪ [ Man Singing In German ]

04:57.935 --> 05:02.564
♪♪ [ Singing Continues ]

05:11.782 --> 05:13.825
[ Ramirez's Voice ]
Remember, Highlander.

05:27.548 --> 05:29.049
Remember?

05:53.950 --> 05:56.451
[ Wind Blowing ]

06:17.974 --> 06:19.891
Free men of the planet, hear me.

06:19.976 --> 06:23.353
We gather together in
secret for the last time.

06:23.437 --> 06:27.983
You suffer under the yoke of General
Katana's rule for the last time.

06:28.067 --> 06:31.444
And you stand without a
leader for the last time.

06:31.529 --> 06:32.988
Will you lead us, Ramirez?

06:33.072 --> 06:35.198
No, I'm not your leader.

06:35.283 --> 06:38.994
But because I see with
eyes different from yours,

06:39.996 --> 06:41.663
I see a man...

06:41.747 --> 06:44.624
with a great destiny before him.

06:44.709 --> 06:47.085
Who is he?
Show him to us!

06:47.169 --> 06:49.087
Let him show himself.

06:51.340 --> 06:54.759
[ Electricity Crackling ]

07:06.480 --> 07:08.732
YES. You.

07:17.575 --> 07:19.576
[ Electricity Crackling ]

07:32.465 --> 07:35.759
[ Crowd Murmuring ]

07:39.221 --> 07:41.514
We are now as one.

07:44.977 --> 07:46.478
How do we start?

07:46.562 --> 07:50.482
Not we. You.
And you start with Katana.

07:50.566 --> 07:52.692
[ Explosion ]

07:52.777 --> 07:55.278
General Katana's attacking!

07:55.363 --> 07:58.031
[ Crowd Shouting ]

07:58.115 --> 08:01.409
♪♪ [ Woman Singing In German ]

08:21.931 --> 08:23.723
[ Ramirez's Voice ]
Remember the rebellion?

08:23.808 --> 08:26.267
The cause is still just...

08:26.352 --> 08:27.644
and still yours.

08:28.771 --> 08:32.315
[ Explosions ]

08:39.823 --> 08:42.366
Break ranks!
Get more men!

08:46.205 --> 08:49.999
♪♪ [ Orchestra: Opera Continues ]

09:02.555 --> 09:05.348
[ Swords Clanging ]

09:44.847 --> 09:48.683
My friends in here remind
me of you and Ramirez.

09:48.767 --> 09:52.479
So deadly in their own
environment, yet...

09:55.024 --> 09:56.983
[ Chuckles ]

09:57.067 --> 09:59.944
so tame and servile in mine.

10:01.572 --> 10:03.406
Maybe they're just waiting.

10:05.910 --> 10:07.160
Waiting for what?

10:07.244 --> 10:09.370
For you to get careless.

10:09.455 --> 10:11.080
Ah.

10:11.707 --> 10:13.416
Maybe they are.

10:15.794 --> 10:19.172
But as of tomorrow, waiting won't
be an option for you, will it?

10:19.256 --> 10:20.798
You sure?

10:24.970 --> 10:26.638
[ Squealing, Bones Cracking ]

10:33.145 --> 10:35.438
[ Laughs ]

10:37.775 --> 10:41.277
♪♪ [ Orchestra Continues ]

11:02.007 --> 11:03.383
Let's get on with it.

11:03.467 --> 11:06.886
The punishment for rebellion is death.

11:06.971 --> 11:11.307
Judge them guilty, and I'll
execute them here, now.

11:11.392 --> 11:14.185
You forget yourself, General Katana.

11:14.270 --> 11:18.606
As you well know, for many years we have
exiled those rebels and criminals...

11:18.691 --> 11:23.069
who, like you, possess
this unholy immortality.

11:23.153 --> 11:26.698
Therefore, I sentence you
both to this same exile—

11:26.782 --> 11:28.825
an exile into the future.

11:28.909 --> 11:32.245
- What?
- Silence, General Katana!

11:32.329 --> 11:36.749
In that distant future, you will face
other Immortals in trial by combat...

11:36.834 --> 11:39.127
from which only one can survive.

11:39.211 --> 11:41.212
And, as is your way,

11:41.297 --> 11:44.591
you will die only when your
head is cut from your body.

11:44.675 --> 11:47.677
- Will we be together?
- Well, not at first.

11:47.761 --> 11:51.264
But we are joined in a way
that can never be broken,

11:51.348 --> 11:53.516
not even by death.

11:53.601 --> 11:57.770
When you need me, you'll
only have to call my name.

11:57.855 --> 11:59.397
I'll always find you.

11:59.481 --> 12:04.319
Finally, the last one to
survive will have a choice.

12:04.403 --> 12:06.112
Choice? What choice?

12:06.196 --> 12:08.406
Grow old and die in the future...

12:08.490 --> 12:11.951
or return here with his
freedom and faith restored.

12:12.036 --> 12:13.578
[ Muttering ]
Priests.

12:15.080 --> 12:17.540
Now go, and remember,

12:17.625 --> 12:20.627
there can be only one.

12:20.711 --> 12:23.379
[ Electricity Crackling ]
[ Both Groaning ]

12:29.845 --> 12:34.015
Okay, Mr MacLeod, the show is over.
[ Chuckles ]

12:34.099 --> 12:36.559
I thought so too, Charlie.

12:37.895 --> 12:42.732
I really did.

12:43.984 --> 12:46.486
[ Thunderclap ]

12:51.659 --> 12:55.703
♪♪ [ Program Theme ] Good evening and
welcome to TSC's nightly report.

12:55.788 --> 12:58.498
Today's satellite readings
from above the shield...

12:58.582 --> 13:01.668
confirm that highly dangerous
levels of ultraviolet radiation...

13:01.752 --> 13:05.630
continue to bombard the planet in
the absence of the ozone layer.

13:05.714 --> 13:09.342
But here below the shield
we are protected and safe.

13:09.426 --> 13:11.135
At a press conference held earlier...

13:11.220 --> 13:15.598
the corporation's chief financial officer,
David Blake, denied growing rumors...

13:15.683 --> 13:17.642
of a management shake-up.

13:17.726 --> 13:21.354
Alan Neyman, president of TSC,
was unavailable for comment...

13:21.438 --> 13:24.273
and he seems increasingly isolated.

13:27.069 --> 13:28.778
[ Dial Tone Beeps ]

13:28.862 --> 13:31.280
Shield Corporation.
May I help you?

13:31.365 --> 13:34.409
Alan Neyman, please.
Who may I say is calling?

13:34.493 --> 13:37.537
Tell him it's a friend.
Tell him it's MacLeod.

13:37.621 --> 13:39.997
Please hold.
Thank you.

13:40.082 --> 13:43.501
I'm sorry. He's not accepting
any calls at the moment.

13:43.585 --> 13:44.919
Any message?

13:45.003 --> 13:47.255
No, no message.

13:47.339 --> 13:49.424
Thank you for calling.
Thank you.

13:54.805 --> 13:56.472
Hey, grandpa!

13:56.557 --> 13:59.726
You got some change for
the oxygen machine?

13:59.810 --> 14:02.854
Hey! Hey, you cheap fuck!

14:03.856 --> 14:05.148
You deaf or what?

14:06.775 --> 14:09.652
You.
You're MacLeod, aren't you?

14:11.113 --> 14:12.655
So what?

14:15.868 --> 14:18.661
Yeah, right. So what?

14:19.705 --> 14:22.039
Okay, okay. Come on.
We're out of here!

14:22.124 --> 14:25.084
- Let's go!
-- Come on, guys! Forget it!

14:25.169 --> 14:27.336
Let's go! Move!

14:43.604 --> 14:45.938
What was that?
What was what?

14:46.023 --> 14:47.815
I heard something.
I'm calling it in.

14:47.900 --> 14:49.317
Security.

14:49.401 --> 14:52.195
[ On Headset ]
I heard something. You see anything?

14:52.279 --> 14:54.947
I don't see nothing.
Could be fish.

14:55.032 --> 14:56.657
Fish live in the lake.

14:56.742 --> 14:58.326
Not in this lake.

14:58.410 --> 14:59.786
Yeah? Well, I've seen 'em.

14:59.870 --> 15:01.829
It was a fish.

16:30.127 --> 16:32.044
[ Man ]
Come on, Louise. Let's do it.

16:33.714 --> 16:35.381
Here it is.

16:37.676 --> 16:39.468
[ Beeping ]

16:39.553 --> 16:41.304
[ Seal Bursts ]

16:53.358 --> 16:55.484
[ Beeping ]

17:00.449 --> 17:03.326
We've got 30 seconds to
get a clear reading.

17:06.288 --> 17:08.873
- [ Beeping ]
- I'm going into the computer.

17:10.876 --> 17:12.627
- [ Beeping ]
- Blue alert!

17:12.711 --> 17:16.297
[ Shouting, Chattering ]

17:16.381 --> 17:19.258
-- Check your monitor!
- Three-zero-point-four-four!

17:19.343 --> 17:24.055
-- [ Beeping Continues ]
- Impossible. Radiation levels can't be normal.

17:26.141 --> 17:27.683
- Go to red!
-- [ Alarm Blaring ]

17:27.768 --> 17:30.645
Come on, Louise. Keep moving.
But you don't know what this means.

17:30.729 --> 17:32.730
You can tell me about it later.

17:34.483 --> 17:36.192
Go, go, go!

17:39.071 --> 17:40.863
Shoot! Shoot!

17:46.787 --> 17:49.372
[ Alarm Continues ]

17:53.085 --> 17:55.378
Let's split up!

18:12.229 --> 18:14.063
♪♪ [ Lounge Jazz ]

18:14.147 --> 18:15.982
[ Man ] ♪ A hurricane hits ♪

18:16.066 --> 18:18.192
♪ Your house is gone ♪

18:18.276 --> 18:21.737
♪ The parakeet flies away ♪

18:22.948 --> 18:26.993
♪ You don't get the raise
you've been counting on ♪

18:27.077 --> 18:30.246
♪ Got gamblin' debts to pay ♪

18:31.248 --> 18:32.915
♪ But you're in— ♪♪

18:35.252 --> 18:36.669
What now, gentlemen?

18:36.753 --> 18:40.047
Isn't that your friend
MacLeod, General?

18:40.132 --> 18:42.967
He's getting older,
but he's still alive.

18:43.051 --> 18:45.177
I know that! I'm not blind!

18:45.262 --> 18:50.182
Good. Then you can also see that
he hasn't made his choice yet.

18:50.267 --> 18:54.145
He still has time to come back to us.

18:54.229 --> 18:55.771
Wonderful.

18:55.856 --> 18:58.566
[ Katana ]
Corda! Reno!

18:58.650 --> 19:00.443
Where are you?

19:03.321 --> 19:04.697
There you are.

19:04.781 --> 19:08.034
I want you to leave for
the future immediately.

19:08.118 --> 19:10.453
Find MacLeod and kill him.

19:10.537 --> 19:13.414
But I thought you said MacLeod
was mortal and will never return.

19:15.333 --> 19:18.085
Do me a big favor, Corda.
Don't think.

19:18.170 --> 19:20.880
He's an old man now.
He'll be dead in a couple of weeks.

19:20.964 --> 19:25.468
I don't care.
Find him for me. Kill him.

19:29.139 --> 19:31.432
[ Katana ]
It's so hard to get good help.

19:31.516 --> 19:33.434
[ Cackling ]

19:43.361 --> 19:46.989
♪♪ [ Pop, Faint ]

19:47.074 --> 19:50.743
♪ Oh, it's a perfect, perfect ♪

19:50.827 --> 19:54.163
♪ Perfect world ♪

19:55.165 --> 19:57.958
♪ My beautiful world ♪

19:59.169 --> 20:02.671
♪ It's a perfect world ♪♪

20:03.924 --> 20:05.424
[ Coin Clatters ]

20:07.594 --> 20:11.514
[ Man ] ♪ One dream, one soul ♪

20:11.598 --> 20:15.184
♪ One prize, one goal ♪

20:15.268 --> 20:16.977
♪ One golden glance ♪

20:17.062 --> 20:19.855
Hey, Jimmy.
Hey, Mr MacLeod.

20:21.650 --> 20:24.443
How you doing?
Good. Good.

20:24.528 --> 20:26.612
All right, all right.

20:26.696 --> 20:28.614
Ousceva?
Ousceva.

20:28.698 --> 20:31.408
[ Laughs ] ♪♪ [ Continues ]

20:31.493 --> 20:33.452
Here you go.
[ Male Announcer On TV ] Good evening.

20:33.537 --> 20:37.957
Reports have just come in of a terrorist
attack on the Shield Control Center.

20:38.041 --> 20:40.876
According to information
available at this time,

20:40.961 --> 20:43.129
the group calling themselves Cobalt...

20:43.213 --> 20:45.840
successfully made an attempt
to enter Shield Control...

20:45.924 --> 20:47.049
for propaganda purposes.

20:47.134 --> 20:49.593
The Shield Corporation
had this comment.

20:49.678 --> 20:51.929
What Cobalt is doing is insanity.

20:52.013 --> 20:53.639
Any tampering with the
shield of any kind...

20:53.723 --> 20:56.433
endangers the lives of every man,
woman and child on the planet.

20:56.518 --> 21:01.147
Cobalt is known to be headed by
environmental terrorist Louise Marcus...

21:01.231 --> 21:03.566
who led the raid and remains
at large at this time.

21:03.650 --> 21:05.401
Pretty girl.

21:05.485 --> 21:06.986
♪♪ [ Continues ]

21:07.070 --> 21:10.656
♪ Is this a kind ♪

21:10.740 --> 21:12.491
♪ Of magic ♪

21:12.576 --> 21:14.326
[ Chorus ] ♪ It's a kind of magic ♪

21:14.411 --> 21:18.622
♪ There can be only one ♪

21:24.713 --> 21:27.381
You're a good boy, Jimmy.
Well, bottoms up.

21:27.465 --> 21:30.467
[ Thunder Rumbling ]
Hey! Are you MacLeod?

21:31.261 --> 21:35.097
Hey, I asked you a question.
Are you MacLeod?

21:35.182 --> 21:37.391
Yes, I am.

21:37.475 --> 21:41.437
Great. I always wanted to meet the
guy that turned the world to shit.

21:41.521 --> 21:43.397
He saved our lives, if you ask me.

21:43.481 --> 21:46.025
I'm not asking you.

21:46.109 --> 21:49.111
Okay. What do you want?

21:49.196 --> 21:53.407
Did you ever think about that
before you covered the sky with that puke?

21:54.534 --> 21:56.911
- Who are you?
- Me?

21:58.246 --> 22:00.623
I'm nobody. All right?

22:01.625 --> 22:04.043
I work all day and my life stinks...

22:04.127 --> 22:07.004
and it's your goddamn
fault, you old bastard.

22:07.088 --> 22:08.631
Don't turn your back on me!

22:08.715 --> 22:10.216
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

22:12.969 --> 22:15.930
There are some people in this world...

22:16.014 --> 22:18.515
who know when to stop...

22:18.600 --> 22:20.601
and some people who don't.

22:21.853 --> 22:23.354
Which kind are you?

22:23.438 --> 22:26.899
Okay, Miss Nobody, you're out of here.

22:26.983 --> 22:29.902
Come on, come on—
Come on! Come on!

22:29.986 --> 22:31.987
You're gone.
I'll see you again.

22:32.072 --> 22:33.781
Anytime.

22:34.950 --> 22:37.701
Oh, Jesus.
Why do they always pick my place?

22:37.786 --> 22:40.412
Know what I'm saying?
I'm sorry, Mr MacLeod.

22:40.497 --> 22:42.331
No problem, Jimmy.
No problem.

22:42.958 --> 22:44.667
Watch out!

22:44.751 --> 22:46.919
Son of a bitch!

22:47.003 --> 22:49.505
Are you all right?
Yeah. Yeah, I'll be fine.

22:49.589 --> 22:52.508
You just hang in there, Mr MacLeod.
I'll be right back.

22:52.592 --> 22:55.844
Hey, you! Come back here!
I'm talking to you!

23:01.393 --> 23:03.477
Maybe I should get this one.

23:07.774 --> 23:10.150
[ Beeping ]

23:10.235 --> 23:12.528
What was that?

23:13.363 --> 23:15.823
[ People Chattering ]

23:15.907 --> 23:18.117
What the hell was that?

23:18.201 --> 23:21.620
[ Electrical Pulses ]

23:38.680 --> 23:40.347
Oh, no.

23:44.019 --> 23:45.644
Not again.

23:45.729 --> 23:48.230
[ People Chattering ]

24:00.327 --> 24:02.828
♪♪ [ Rock: Muffled, Indistinct ]

24:04.247 --> 24:05.622
Mr MacLeod?

24:06.624 --> 24:08.042
Yes?

24:08.126 --> 24:09.877
I'm Louise Marcus.

24:11.796 --> 24:13.922
Terror is a dangerous
business, Ms Marcus.

24:14.007 --> 24:15.466
I'm not a terrorist.

24:15.550 --> 24:19.178
Well, whatever you are, Ms Marcus,
you'll have to excuse me.

24:19.262 --> 24:21.388
I had some very disturbing news.

24:21.473 --> 24:22.598
Did somebody die?

24:23.433 --> 24:25.851
Unfortunately not.

24:25.935 --> 24:27.644
Good-bye, Ms. Marcus.

24:28.646 --> 24:30.689
You know, I used to read about you.

24:30.774 --> 24:34.651
You had such great
passion for the world.

24:34.736 --> 24:36.862
I admired you.

24:36.946 --> 24:39.114
I can see that's all gone now.

24:39.949 --> 24:42.534
You're nothing but a tired old man.

24:42.619 --> 24:44.328
More than you know.

24:48.541 --> 24:50.125
Oh, no, you don't.

24:55.673 --> 24:57.633
The world is dying, MacLeod.

24:57.717 --> 24:59.885
I need your help.

24:59.969 --> 25:02.012
Please get out of the car.

25:03.014 --> 25:04.473
No way.

25:05.892 --> 25:07.935
Suit yourself.

25:08.019 --> 25:09.686
[ Engine Starts ]

25:16.820 --> 25:17.986
[ Horn Honks ]

25:18.071 --> 25:22.741
Listen, MacLeod, when I broke in tonight,
the numbers and figures I saw didn't add up.

25:22.826 --> 25:25.077
Something's wrong, and Blake's
trying to cover it up.

25:25.161 --> 25:27.329
- What do you want me to do?
- Help me.

25:27.414 --> 25:29.289
I can't. Not now.

25:29.374 --> 25:32.251
What happened to the MacLeod
that everyone believed in?

25:32.335 --> 25:34.670
That was 40 years ago.
I'm an old man.

25:34.754 --> 25:37.840
- [ Groaning ]
- Are you all right? What's the matter?

25:40.218 --> 25:41.343
You gotta go.

25:42.637 --> 25:44.221
[ Tires Squeal ]

25:55.024 --> 25:58.360
[ Corda, Reno Yelping, Cackling ]

26:00.530 --> 26:02.614
Who are they?

26:02.699 --> 26:03.824
I don't know.

26:03.908 --> 26:05.826
[ Distorted ]
MacLeod!

26:05.910 --> 26:07.870
Was that just a lucky guess?

26:09.622 --> 26:11.540
Wait a minute.
What are we doing?

26:11.624 --> 26:14.793
Get in there.
Don't make a sound. In here?

26:14.878 --> 26:17.087
You've gotta be kidding.
Come on!

26:19.382 --> 26:21.633
Let me have him.
But I want him!

26:21.718 --> 26:23.385
It's my turn.

26:23.470 --> 26:24.720
MacLeod!

26:25.638 --> 26:29.933
You're going to die!

26:36.941 --> 26:39.401
[ Panting ]

26:39.486 --> 26:42.362
Ramirez!
My old friend Ramirez!

26:53.458 --> 26:55.250
[ Cackles ]

27:04.052 --> 27:06.053
[ Hisses ]

27:12.101 --> 27:14.102
[ Metal Bar Clanks ]
Thank you!

27:31.329 --> 27:33.789
[ Siren Wailing ]

27:39.963 --> 27:42.798
- [ Cackling ]
- [ Grunts ]

28:15.123 --> 28:16.832
[ Groans ]

28:25.008 --> 28:27.634
[ Train Horn Blows ]

28:41.566 --> 28:43.317
[ Yells ]

28:48.323 --> 28:51.366
[ Grunting ]

28:51.451 --> 28:54.036
[ Horn Blowing ]

29:14.474 --> 29:15.724
[ Screams ]

29:26.903 --> 29:29.655
[ Electricity Crackling ]

29:43.419 --> 29:46.755
[ Groaning ]

29:50.510 --> 29:52.260
MacLeod.

29:54.681 --> 29:57.808
[ Groaning ]

30:16.828 --> 30:18.829
[ Yelping ]

30:23.209 --> 30:25.293
[ Groaning ]

30:41.352 --> 30:44.646
[ Cackling ]

31:00.246 --> 31:02.497
[ Mouthing Words ]

31:31.652 --> 31:32.903
[ Groans ]

32:27.333 --> 32:29.209
[ Yelling ]

32:47.395 --> 32:48.812
[ Tires Screech ]

33:01.993 --> 33:04.995
I hate to say good-bye, Highlander!

33:05.079 --> 33:06.955
Why?
Are you going somewhere?

33:26.976 --> 33:28.977
Hey, pal, you got a light?

33:29.770 --> 33:31.146
Thanks.

33:32.481 --> 33:34.190
[ Cackling ]

34:06.098 --> 34:08.058
Come on.

34:08.141 --> 34:10.143
Come on!

34:42.717 --> 34:49.556
Ramirez!

34:49.641 --> 34:52.768
[ Groaning ]

34:52.853 --> 34:57.440
Ramirez!

35:04.198 --> 35:07.325
Alas, poor Yorick.

35:07.410 --> 35:10.370
[ Electrical Pulses ]
I knew him, Horatio.

35:10.454 --> 35:12.247
A fellow of infinite jest.

35:13.290 --> 35:14.874
Ah!

35:14.959 --> 35:17.377
[ Audience Chuckling, Murmuring ]

35:18.838 --> 35:21.381
[ Ramirez ]
Well, now.

35:24.093 --> 35:26.052
Alas, poor Yorick.

35:26.137 --> 35:28.304
I knew him, Horatio.

35:28.389 --> 35:31.307
Actually, the name is Ramirez.

35:31.392 --> 35:35.603
- Will you get out of here.
- Excuse me?

35:35.688 --> 35:38.565
A fellow of infinite jest,

35:38.649 --> 35:41.359
of most excellent fancy.

35:41.444 --> 35:45.113
Forgive me for interrupting
your conversation but--

35:45.197 --> 35:49.284
He hath borne me upon his
back a thousand times.

35:49.368 --> 35:55.248
Now, how abhorred in
my imagination it is.

35:55.332 --> 35:57.917
My gorge rises at it.

35:58.002 --> 36:00.086
Here hung those lips...

36:00.171 --> 36:04.007
that I have kissed I know not how oft.

36:04.091 --> 36:09.304
Sir, whatever you gentlemen felt for each
other when your friend was still alive...

36:09.388 --> 36:11.389
is certainly none of my affair.

36:13.642 --> 36:15.727
What's your fucking game, shithead?

36:15.811 --> 36:18.229
[ Audience Laughing ] Shithead?

36:18.314 --> 36:19.814
What's a shithead?

36:19.899 --> 36:21.816
Get off the stage!

36:21.901 --> 36:24.986
[ Audience Continues Laughing ]

36:30.451 --> 36:33.286
[ Laughs ] My apologies!

36:34.497 --> 36:36.915
Enough of this useless banter.

36:36.999 --> 36:41.920
I shall be on my way and leave
you to converse with your skull.

36:42.004 --> 36:44.005
Farewell, dear shithead.

36:46.133 --> 36:47.592
Farewell.

36:47.676 --> 36:50.011
[ Cheering ]

37:08.697 --> 37:10.740
Rather glad the magic works.

37:12.701 --> 37:14.828
[ Horn Honking ]

37:20.459 --> 37:22.919
So much for the horse and cart.

37:29.260 --> 37:31.052
[ MacLeod ] Louise.

37:54.869 --> 37:56.578
Who are you?

38:00.040 --> 38:02.584
I'm Connor MacLeod
of the Clan MacLeod.

38:07.423 --> 38:08.798
And I cannot die.

38:39.663 --> 38:42.582
I'm Louise Marcus from
Flagstaff, Arizona.

39:32.007 --> 39:34.592
Let me just see if I
can get this straight.

39:34.677 --> 39:38.596
You're mortal there, but
you're immortal here...

39:38.681 --> 39:41.849
until you kill all the guys
from there who have come here,

39:43.185 --> 39:44.978
and then you're mortal here.

39:45.980 --> 39:48.856
Unless you go back there...

39:48.941 --> 39:51.484
or some more guys
from there come here,

39:51.568 --> 39:56.364
in which case you become
immortal here... again.

39:56.448 --> 39:58.908
- Something like that.
- Of course.

39:58.993 --> 40:00.702
It would be something
like that, wouldn't it?

40:02.705 --> 40:04.706
Quite a night.
Tell me about it.

40:04.790 --> 40:06.624
Think I do this every Saturday night?

40:06.709 --> 40:08.584
Let's say it's a kind of magic.

40:09.628 --> 40:11.838
That's not what I was talking about.

40:11.922 --> 40:14.590
So, what do you want me to do?

40:15.342 --> 40:19.012
You built the shield. Maybe you can
figure out what's going on up there.

40:19.972 --> 40:24.976
What are you saying?
Something is being kept very, very quiet.

40:25.060 --> 40:28.021
Even your old pal Alan
is on a tight leash.

40:28.105 --> 40:30.023
I couldn't get anyone to listen to me.

40:30.107 --> 40:31.941
So you started Cobalt.

40:32.651 --> 40:35.778
Got your face on national TV.

40:35.863 --> 40:37.280
Well, of course.

40:37.364 --> 40:39.699
Somebody had to get
people's attention,

40:39.783 --> 40:42.994
start asking questions,
find out the truth.

40:43.078 --> 40:44.287
Someone like you?

40:44.371 --> 40:46.372
No, damn it!

40:47.875 --> 40:49.709
Someone like you.

41:15.986 --> 41:17.653
Excellent threads, dude.

41:20.991 --> 41:22.450
Shithead.

41:32.961 --> 41:35.963
[ Chattering ]

41:39.760 --> 41:41.302
May I help you, sir?

41:41.387 --> 41:42.970
I would like a suit of clothes.

41:43.055 --> 41:44.680
And why not, indeed?

41:44.765 --> 41:48.518
We are the oldest gentlemen's
tailor in Scotland.

41:48.602 --> 41:51.270
Well, then, I've come
to the right place...

41:51.355 --> 41:53.815
since I am, without a doubt, the
oldest gentleman in Scotland.

41:55.359 --> 41:58.403
Well, if you say so, sir.

41:58.487 --> 41:59.821
Well, let's get started.

41:59.905 --> 42:03.032
I have a long journey ahead
of me and limited time.

42:04.034 --> 42:07.328
I'm afraid sir still
doesn't understand.

42:07.996 --> 42:11.582
A suit may take several
weeks to complete.

42:11.667 --> 42:15.253
I'm afraid sir damn
well does understand...

42:15.337 --> 42:18.339
and sir would like a
suit of clothes by 3:00.

42:22.594 --> 42:25.721
♪♪ [ "William Tell Overture" ]

43:04.219 --> 43:07.388
There is nothing like a challenge
to bring out the best in man.

43:10.767 --> 43:12.560
With our compliments, sir.

43:14.354 --> 43:16.772
Thank you, Roy.

43:16.857 --> 43:19.358
Can we arrange a limo for you, sir?

43:19.443 --> 43:22.195
A limo?
Yes, to take you to the airport.

43:23.447 --> 43:24.697
Airport?

43:24.781 --> 43:27.992
You did say you had a long
journey ahead of you.

43:28.076 --> 43:31.746
Yes. Well, I believe the
fastest way is still to fly.

43:33.248 --> 43:35.500
To fly.

43:35.584 --> 43:37.210
Yes, of course.

43:41.215 --> 43:42.423
To fly.

44:03.529 --> 44:05.738
[ Louise ]
Have you ever seen a blue sky?

44:08.784 --> 44:10.409
Sure.

44:12.412 --> 44:14.080
What was it like?

44:22.172 --> 44:23.506
It was--

44:26.468 --> 44:29.053
It was the deepest blue you ever saw.

44:30.639 --> 44:32.807
But it was more than that.

44:35.310 --> 44:38.813
White clouds suddenly
turning dark with rain.

44:41.984 --> 44:44.902
[ Sighs, Chuckles ]

44:44.987 --> 44:47.822
And the smell of grass
after the storm.

44:51.493 --> 44:53.369
Red leaves in fall.

44:55.080 --> 44:56.747
Snow in winter.

44:59.418 --> 45:01.002
It was beautiful.

45:10.637 --> 45:13.014
And we thought it would last forever.

45:22.816 --> 45:25.234
I wish you could have seen it.

45:28.196 --> 45:29.864
So do I.

45:34.411 --> 45:36.203
I'd like to,

45:38.040 --> 45:40.458
just once before I die.

45:53.305 --> 45:56.557
[ Katana ] Ah, yes.

45:57.142 --> 45:58.934
Yes.

46:07.319 --> 46:09.779
I guess if you want something done,

46:11.448 --> 46:13.199
you have to do it yourself.

46:23.043 --> 46:27.004
[ Male Announcer ] It's the wackiest
show on TV— The Psychic Cook.

46:27.089 --> 46:30.549
Step into the paranormal pantry
with the special guest ghost...

46:30.634 --> 46:33.803
and prepare meals from
beyond the grave.

46:33.887 --> 46:36.514
Spooky sauces to ghostly goulashes--

46:36.598 --> 46:38.808
It's a whole lot of fun!

46:38.892 --> 46:40.893
The Psychic Cook, weekdays at 5:00.

46:40.977 --> 46:43.104
Brought to you by Xenon,

46:43.188 --> 46:45.731
the world's highest grade
of non-emission gasoline,

46:45.816 --> 46:48.025
available at service
stations everywhere.

46:48.110 --> 46:50.194
Only $55 a gallon.

47:11.800 --> 47:14.343
[ Mutters In Foreign Language ]
It happens again!

47:20.142 --> 47:23.477
[ Passengers Screaming, Shouting ]

47:24.146 --> 47:25.980
[ Electricity Crackling, Faint ]

47:42.998 --> 47:44.331
[ Grunts ]

47:44.416 --> 47:47.084
That was great! Yes!

47:47.169 --> 47:48.711
[ Yells ]

47:48.795 --> 47:51.505
[ Exhales ]

47:52.841 --> 47:54.759
Where the hell am I?

47:58.430 --> 48:00.431
[ Laughs ]

48:00.515 --> 48:04.018
This sure doesn't look
like Kansas, does it?

48:05.187 --> 48:08.355
[ People Screaming ]
Godzilla! Godzilla!

48:13.320 --> 48:16.447
[ Passengers Exclaiming ]
[ Blows Landing ]

48:16.531 --> 48:18.657
[ Woman ]
Oh, my God!

48:19.993 --> 48:22.787
[ Woman Gasps ]

48:22.871 --> 48:24.413
Oh, God.

48:27.417 --> 48:29.043
[ Man ]
Did you see what he did?

48:37.594 --> 48:39.178
Look out!

48:42.682 --> 48:44.683
You're a little one, aren't you?

48:46.144 --> 48:48.103
[ Grunts ]
[ Chuckles ]

48:48.188 --> 48:51.065
Bet you've always wanted
to drive one of these, huh?

48:52.442 --> 48:53.984
Me too.

48:58.281 --> 48:59.782
Hi!

49:03.036 --> 49:05.079
- [ Groans ]
- [ Chuckles ]

49:21.096 --> 49:23.639
- [ Chortling ]
- [ Yelling ]

49:28.770 --> 49:30.229
Yes!

49:34.317 --> 49:38.404
- [ Passengers Screaming ]
- [ Yelling ]

49:43.451 --> 49:45.411
[ Laughing ]

49:47.664 --> 49:50.291
[ Screaming ]

49:52.711 --> 49:54.503
Give me more!

50:04.306 --> 50:07.808
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Screaming ]

50:16.902 --> 50:18.652
Let's have some fun!

50:44.554 --> 50:45.971
Oh, my God!

51:05.533 --> 51:08.243
Last stop.
[ Chuckles ]

51:08.328 --> 51:11.330
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

51:42.404 --> 51:43.904
[ Beeps ]

51:50.412 --> 51:53.080
[ Coughs, Sighs ]

51:54.416 --> 51:58.002
Can't even make a decent
cup of coffee anymore.

51:58.086 --> 52:00.254
You always use too much water.

52:01.256 --> 52:03.507
- Mac?
- Alan.

52:03.591 --> 52:06.552
Where the hell have you been?

52:07.971 --> 52:10.014
I'm so glad you're here.

52:10.098 --> 52:13.809
So many things have happened.
We must talk.

52:13.893 --> 52:15.269
Okay.

52:15.353 --> 52:17.104
Good God.

52:20.400 --> 52:22.735
You look fantastic.

52:24.029 --> 52:26.780
What have you been doing?
Working out?

52:29.868 --> 52:32.119
Have you had a face lift?

52:32.203 --> 52:34.246
Something like that.

52:38.960 --> 52:41.545
Do you remember
the dreams we had?

52:58.480 --> 53:00.314
Remember the day?

53:00.398 --> 53:05.319
[ Man's Voice ] Good evening. Only a few months
now until the ozone layer is completely gone.

53:05.403 --> 53:08.864
A team of international scientists
led by Dr Alan Neyman...

53:08.948 --> 53:10.783
and supervised by Connor MacLeod...

53:10.867 --> 53:12.284
work around the clock.

53:12.368 --> 53:15.662
This may be the last
chance for planet Earth.

53:15.747 --> 53:18.540
This is TSC.
We are standing by for shield launch.

53:18.625 --> 53:21.627
[ Camera Shutter Clicking ]

53:25.131 --> 53:29.134
They'll remember this day
for a thousand years--

53:29.219 --> 53:32.096
The day we protected the
planet from the sun.

53:32.180 --> 53:34.848
[ Man On P.A. ]
All personnel please leave the area.

53:34.933 --> 53:37.601
We are starting the final countdown.

53:39.979 --> 53:45.317
All personnel please leave the area.
We are starting final countdown.

53:45.985 --> 53:49.613
[ Man #1 ] TSC, this is Florida Control.
All power for the shield—

53:49.697 --> 53:52.491
[ Man #2 ] All systems are go.
Please run final checks on all shield power elements.

53:52.575 --> 53:57.287
[ Man On P.A. ] All personnel please leave the area.
We are starting the final countdown.

54:07.924 --> 54:10.425
[ Man #2 ]
TSC, this is Houston Space Control.

54:10.510 --> 54:14.888
Satellite is in final receiving position.
You can start final countdown.

54:16.933 --> 54:18.725
Stand by. This is it.

54:18.810 --> 54:20.811
Roger, Control.
We are standing by.

54:20.895 --> 54:22.354
This is it!

54:28.653 --> 54:30.612
Florida Control, this is TSC.

54:30.697 --> 54:33.866
The December shield installation
is ready to receive.

54:33.950 --> 54:37.911
To all power sources around
the world, this is TSC.

54:37.996 --> 54:39.621
We are ready to receive.

54:43.251 --> 54:46.003
[ Man On P.A. ] Launch minus 10
Ten seconds and counting.

54:46.087 --> 54:50.048
Okay, boys, let's make this a good one.
The world is watching.

54:50.133 --> 54:54.761
[ Man On P.A. ]
Four, three, two, one.

54:54.846 --> 54:56.346
Ignition!

55:17.911 --> 55:20.412
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

55:32.717 --> 55:34.718
What a day.

55:34.802 --> 55:36.762
What a great day.

55:38.389 --> 55:41.058
It was a great idea, wasn't it, Mac?

55:41.142 --> 55:42.684
It still is.

55:43.728 --> 55:45.312
But you don't know what's happened.

55:47.065 --> 55:48.232
[ Alan On lntercom ]
It's wonderful.

55:48.316 --> 55:50.025
Alan— Come here.
Let me show you.

55:50.109 --> 55:52.027
Shh, shh, shh, shh.
Come on.

55:52.111 --> 55:54.279
[ Typing ]

56:33.278 --> 56:35.487
[ Door Opens ]

56:36.447 --> 56:41.201
Forgive me, Alan.
I didn't realize you got in this early.

56:41.286 --> 56:45.664
Not usually,
but we got to talking.

56:45.748 --> 56:49.543
Forgive me.
David Blake, Connor MacLeod.

56:49.627 --> 56:52.045
Oh, yes, of course.

56:52.130 --> 56:54.548
I'm afraid I'd forgotten
you were still alive.

56:54.632 --> 56:56.717
Always.

56:57.719 --> 56:59.511
Something on the computer?

57:00.221 --> 57:02.180
Oh, no. No, no.

57:02.265 --> 57:04.725
Nothing I won't remember.
I hope so.

57:04.809 --> 57:08.854
Alan, as long as we have you here, we might
just as well get off to an early start.

57:08.938 --> 57:10.188
Fine.
My office?

57:10.273 --> 57:11.857
All right.

57:12.900 --> 57:16.069
Mr MacLeod, I'm terribly sorry
to have to break this up.

57:16.154 --> 57:18.697
But I trust you can
find your own way out.

57:18.781 --> 57:21.491
Sure.
Take care of yourself, Alan.

57:25.413 --> 57:28.790
By the way, how is the shield business?
Never better.

57:28.875 --> 57:32.836
It must be great to have every country
in the world as your customer.

57:32.920 --> 57:34.921
Actually, Mr MacLeod,

57:35.006 --> 57:37.924
we prefer to think that we protect
the population of the planet...

57:38.009 --> 57:41.303
from death by solar radiation.

57:41.387 --> 57:44.097
It is a rather unique service.
Don't you agree?

57:44.182 --> 57:45.974
As long as it's necessary.

57:46.059 --> 57:47.351
Meaning?

57:47.435 --> 57:51.021
Maybe one day the ozone
layer will repair itself.

57:51.105 --> 57:54.858
That would indeed be a great day
for the human race, wouldn't it?

57:56.027 --> 57:59.112
But it really makes no
difference anymore...

57:59.197 --> 58:01.615
since you built the
shield to last forever.

58:02.367 --> 58:04.451
Nothing lasts forever.

58:06.996 --> 58:09.331
[ Chuckling ]

58:14.629 --> 58:18.298
♪♪ [ Rock: Man Singing, Indistinct ]

58:20.385 --> 58:23.553
♪♪ [ Continues On Earphones ] My name's Jerry
Pritchard, man. What do they call you?

58:23.638 --> 58:27.641
It's quite comfortable back here.
Rather like a coffin.

58:27.725 --> 58:31.144
Right. People in this town, they'd
kill you for a nickel, man.

58:31.229 --> 58:34.815
- Hey, cabbie, you want some?
- Get the fuck away from my car!

58:34.899 --> 58:36.942
Scumbags! Scumbags!

58:37.026 --> 58:38.026
Really.

58:38.111 --> 58:40.237
You're in the music
business, aren't you?

58:41.406 --> 58:44.199
Call it a hunch.
I knew that.

58:52.667 --> 58:54.584
So you're in the music business, man.
That's cool.

58:54.669 --> 58:57.629
I wish I was in the music business.
My sister was in the music business.

58:57.713 --> 58:59.423
You should meet her.
I think you'd get along.

58:59.507 --> 59:01.633
- Stop now.
- What? Here?

59:01.717 --> 59:03.927
- Now.
- This is good.

59:04.011 --> 59:05.595
This is a good place to stop.

59:07.056 --> 59:09.349
Goddamn! Whoo!

59:09.434 --> 59:12.227
Shit! Fuck! Yeah!

59:15.440 --> 59:17.732
[ Katana ]
I'll get out here.

59:17.817 --> 59:19.776
Oh, wow!
[ Laughing ]

59:19.861 --> 59:22.863
Yeah!
Out of control!

59:22.947 --> 59:25.365
You and my sister, man—
Forget it!

59:25.450 --> 59:28.785
I should introduce you two.
You could sit around and...

59:28.870 --> 59:30.871
compare tattoos or something, man.

59:30.955 --> 59:32.789
You're crazy!

59:36.461 --> 59:38.295
What next, man?

59:40.631 --> 59:43.300
Central, this is Jerry Pritchard!

59:43.384 --> 59:47.053
Hello? Hello? Shit, man.
I should have stayed in school.

59:47.138 --> 59:49.055
Central, hello? I've got—

59:49.140 --> 59:51.141
Just take it easy, all right?

59:51.225 --> 59:55.145
Come on— Come on.
Central! Central!

59:56.564 --> 59:57.898
Shit, man.

01:00:04.113 --> 01:00:06.239
Put all this on my tab.

01:00:06.324 --> 01:00:09.993
And, Jerry, add a little
something for yourself.

01:00:10.786 --> 01:00:12.704
[ Air Hissing ]

01:00:16.918 --> 01:00:26.009
Yes.

01:00:33.518 --> 01:00:35.602
Forgive me asking yet again,

01:00:35.686 --> 01:00:39.439
but how do we remain so high
above the Earth with safety?

01:00:39.524 --> 01:00:41.107
By drinking!

01:00:41.192 --> 01:00:43.527
[ Laughing ]

01:00:45.530 --> 01:00:48.949
♪♪ [ Fanfare ]

01:00:49.700 --> 01:00:52.285
Welcome to your Transatlantic flight.

01:00:52.370 --> 01:00:54.079
Please fasten your seat belts.

01:00:57.416 --> 01:00:59.960
In the unlikely event of a
loss of cabin pressure,

01:01:00.044 --> 01:01:02.295
oxygen masks will drop
from the ceiling.

01:01:02.380 --> 01:01:05.966
Place it over your mouth and
nose, and breathe normally.

01:01:07.426 --> 01:01:09.719
In case of fire, please do not panic.

01:01:09.804 --> 01:01:12.847
Place smoke hood over your head
and crawl to your nearest exit.

01:01:20.690 --> 01:01:24.025
Thank you for flying with
us, and enjoy your flight.

01:01:38.958 --> 01:01:40.500
Ah.

01:01:43.337 --> 01:01:45.463
My kind of town.

01:01:45.548 --> 01:01:48.049
[ Electrical Pulses ]

01:01:49.302 --> 01:01:51.094
I'm waiting, MacLeod.

01:01:55.725 --> 01:01:57.559
Come to me.

01:02:00.938 --> 01:02:03.440
[ Shouts ]
I'm waiting!

01:02:07.445 --> 01:02:09.863
But on the contrary, Virginia,

01:02:09.947 --> 01:02:13.366
all of the most beautiful
women had dark hair.

01:02:13.451 --> 01:02:18.038
Helen of Troy, Cleopatra,
Nefertiti, Joan of Arc,

01:02:18.122 --> 01:02:20.540
to name but a few.

01:02:20.625 --> 01:02:24.544
In fact, it's well known that
the dark-haired ladies...

01:02:24.629 --> 01:02:26.254
like to sit— [ Whispering ]

01:02:26.339 --> 01:02:28.006
[ Giggling ]

01:02:30.051 --> 01:02:31.426
Would you like to order something?

01:02:31.510 --> 01:02:33.303
Thank you.
May I have some water, please?

01:02:33.387 --> 01:02:35.221
Of course.
Something else for you, sir?

01:02:35.306 --> 01:02:38.433
No, thank you.
I never eat anything I cannot identify.

01:02:38.517 --> 01:02:40.018
Ah. Thank you.

01:02:44.148 --> 01:02:46.066
That's not entirely true, of course.

01:02:46.150 --> 01:02:47.734
[ Giggles ]

01:02:51.822 --> 01:02:56.034
[ Woman's Voice ] Forgive me, my
husband, for leaving you so soon.

01:02:56.911 --> 01:02:59.037
I'm so scared, Connor.

01:03:03.000 --> 01:03:06.086
I wanted to stay and love you.

01:03:06.170 --> 01:03:08.254
The sun is killing us.

01:03:08.339 --> 01:03:11.174
Help the ones that are still alive.

01:03:13.177 --> 01:03:15.428
Hold my hand.

01:03:15.513 --> 01:03:17.180
Promise me, Connor.

01:03:19.016 --> 01:03:20.517
Anything.

01:03:22.019 --> 01:03:24.979
Promise me you'll do
something to stop this.

01:03:25.064 --> 01:03:27.357
Aye, love. I will.

01:03:27.441 --> 01:03:29.818
[ Gasping ]

01:03:33.114 --> 01:03:36.116
[ Exhales ]

01:03:37.368 --> 01:03:39.119
I love you.

01:04:01.142 --> 01:04:03.643
[ Muffled Groaning ]

01:04:18.659 --> 01:04:21.536
[ MacLeod ]
It was all going to be so good, so clean.

01:04:21.620 --> 01:04:23.955
And for one brief moment, it was.

01:04:25.416 --> 01:04:28.334
I used to wish you were here to see it.

01:04:28.419 --> 01:04:30.920
But not anymore.

01:04:31.005 --> 01:04:32.922
Not after what it's become,

01:04:33.924 --> 01:04:35.508
what it's done to us.

01:04:35.593 --> 01:04:37.010
[ Clapping ]

01:04:37.094 --> 01:04:40.263
Bravo. Bravo.

01:04:40.347 --> 01:04:42.599
Excellent.

01:04:42.683 --> 01:04:46.352
I always did admire a man
who could talk to the dead.

01:04:52.943 --> 01:04:55.945
It's so good to see
you again, MacLeod.

01:04:58.282 --> 01:05:00.074
The remains of your mortal wife?

01:05:00.910 --> 01:05:02.243
So frail.

01:05:02.870 --> 01:05:04.704
So very dead.

01:05:05.706 --> 01:05:07.373
At least she's at peace.

01:05:08.125 --> 01:05:10.210
Peace is highly overrated.

01:05:10.294 --> 01:05:12.629
Things don't change, Katana.

01:05:12.713 --> 01:05:14.964
I like that.

01:05:15.049 --> 01:05:18.593
After all these years,
you're still a jerk.

01:05:19.970 --> 01:05:21.387
What do you mean?

01:05:21.472 --> 01:05:26.226
After all this time, I was ready
to kick back, grow old and die.

01:05:26.977 --> 01:05:30.355
You changed everything.

01:05:30.439 --> 01:05:32.941
And now I'm back to square one.

01:05:33.025 --> 01:05:34.526
Immortal... again.

01:05:35.986 --> 01:05:39.155
[ Bell Tolling ] So, Katana, let's
see who goes back after all.

01:05:39.240 --> 01:05:41.866
[ Priest Praying In Latin ]

01:05:41.951 --> 01:05:43.409
Mmm.

01:05:43.494 --> 01:05:46.246
I rather like this place.

01:05:46.330 --> 01:05:48.373
It's got atmosphere.

01:05:48.457 --> 01:05:50.333
I just might stay.

01:05:50.417 --> 01:05:52.794
Get off!

01:05:52.878 --> 01:05:55.255
Remember the golden rule, Highlander.

01:05:55.339 --> 01:05:57.674
We must never fight on holy ground.

01:05:58.968 --> 01:06:00.468
And this...

01:06:01.262 --> 01:06:02.554
is holy ground.

01:06:02.638 --> 01:06:06.266
[ Praying Continues ]

01:06:07.309 --> 01:06:09.060
Ashes to ashes,

01:06:09.144 --> 01:06:10.770
dust to dust.

01:06:10.855 --> 01:06:14.691
If you don't take it out and
use it, it's going to rust.

01:06:19.947 --> 01:06:22.782
[ Wind Blowing ]

01:07:01.196 --> 01:07:03.323
On three!
Break!

01:07:03.407 --> 01:07:07.911
Red 36, Blue 21!
Hike! Hike! Hike!

01:07:18.464 --> 01:07:21.841
[ MacLeod's Voice ]
Ship's log: The Rosemary.

01:07:21.926 --> 01:07:26.512
The men are all gone now,
God rest their souls.

01:07:26.597 --> 01:07:30.850
I alone have come back from the dead...
again.

01:07:30.935 --> 01:07:34.187
Who knows how long I
will continue to drift--

01:07:34.271 --> 01:07:37.649
days, months, years?

01:07:37.733 --> 01:07:42.028
As of this day--
September 6, 1853—

01:07:42.112 --> 01:07:45.198
Captain MacLeod no longer exists.

01:07:45.282 --> 01:07:47.283
Will this never end?

01:07:47.368 --> 01:07:49.702
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

01:08:10.474 --> 01:08:13.184
[ Wings Flapping ]

01:08:52.683 --> 01:08:55.059
[ Man Screams ]

01:09:54.995 --> 01:09:57.163
[ Both Grunting ]

01:10:05.631 --> 01:10:06.798
[ Katana Groans ]

01:10:11.678 --> 01:10:13.179
Not bad.

01:11:00.769 --> 01:11:02.687
[ Groans ]

01:11:03.522 --> 01:11:06.524
[ Yells, Grunts ]

01:11:27.421 --> 01:11:29.463
[ Grunts, Laughs ]

01:12:18.555 --> 01:12:20.181
[ Laughing ]

01:12:20.265 --> 01:12:21.933
[ Gasps ]
[ Neck Cracking ]

01:12:22.017 --> 01:12:23.935
Nicely played, MacLeod,

01:12:24.019 --> 01:12:26.270
but the game's not over yet.

01:12:26.355 --> 01:12:29.398
[ Bones Cracking ]

01:12:29.483 --> 01:12:31.108
[ Groans ]

01:12:32.319 --> 01:12:34.737
[ Yells ]

01:12:37.991 --> 01:12:41.160
[ Katana Laughing ]

01:13:03.433 --> 01:13:06.102
What happened to you?
Are you all right?

01:13:06.186 --> 01:13:08.020
I'm fine.

01:13:12.943 --> 01:13:14.860
Who is the girl in the painting?

01:13:17.823 --> 01:13:20.074
That was Heather--

01:13:20.158 --> 01:13:22.201
my first wife.

01:13:22.286 --> 01:13:25.037
We lived in Scotland in 1542.

01:13:27.708 --> 01:13:29.709
What was she like?

01:13:30.919 --> 01:13:35.589
Full of love. Full of life.
Till the end.

01:13:37.426 --> 01:13:40.303
I held her in my arms when she died.

01:13:41.555 --> 01:13:43.639
An old woman.

01:13:43.724 --> 01:13:45.474
I still loved her.

01:13:49.146 --> 01:13:51.230
And the other?

01:13:51.315 --> 01:13:55.109
That's Brenda— my last wife.

01:13:55.193 --> 01:13:56.694
She looks lovely.

01:13:58.572 --> 01:14:00.656
She was.

01:14:00.741 --> 01:14:03.451
She died in New York, 29 years ago.

01:14:04.828 --> 01:14:07.455
That's a long time to be alone.

01:14:08.457 --> 01:14:11.083
You get used to it.

01:14:11.168 --> 01:14:13.336
Do you really?

01:14:13.420 --> 01:14:15.046
No.

01:14:21.178 --> 01:14:22.720
What is it?

01:14:24.765 --> 01:14:26.932
Oh, no. Not again.

01:14:27.017 --> 01:14:28.684
Go upstairs.

01:14:30.520 --> 01:14:32.021
Damn.

01:15:06.431 --> 01:15:09.141
Greetings, Highlander.
You called?

01:15:12.562 --> 01:15:14.563
Incredible.

01:15:14.648 --> 01:15:17.233
What took you so long?
They could have killed me.

01:15:17.317 --> 01:15:19.235
Don't be ridiculous.

01:15:30.664 --> 01:15:32.748
You've remembered almost
everything I taught you.

01:15:32.833 --> 01:15:35.668
I've had a lot of practice lately.

01:15:43.093 --> 01:15:44.969
There's no substitute for experience.

01:15:45.053 --> 01:15:48.472
What experience?
You've been dead for 500 years.

01:15:48.557 --> 01:15:50.224
- So?
- Watch it!

01:15:51.226 --> 01:15:52.726
Watch what?
"Watch what?"

01:15:52.811 --> 01:15:55.271
The sculpture!

01:15:55.355 --> 01:15:57.690
That's a sculpture?

01:15:57.774 --> 01:15:59.817
Now you are being ridiculous.

01:16:20.714 --> 01:16:24.049
Remember, MacLeod— you called me.

01:16:28.930 --> 01:16:29.597
Hmm?

01:16:29.681 --> 01:16:31.724
[ Laughing ]

01:16:41.359 --> 01:16:43.319
To magic.
Magic works.

01:16:48.116 --> 01:16:52.244
It's nice to see that some things have
actually improved over the years.

01:16:52.329 --> 01:16:53.829
Is this private?

01:16:53.914 --> 01:16:56.582
[ Ramirez ]
Not necessarily.

01:16:56.666 --> 01:16:58.751
This is Juan Sanchez
Villa-Lobos Ramirez,

01:16:58.835 --> 01:17:01.795
my old friend and teacher,
visiting from Scotland.

01:17:01.880 --> 01:17:04.465
Visiting most unexpectedly
from Scotland.

01:17:04.549 --> 01:17:06.509
This is Louise Marcus.

01:17:06.593 --> 01:17:08.928
Watch it.
She's wanted by the police.

01:17:09.012 --> 01:17:12.431
I didn't realize the police
had such good taste.

01:17:12.516 --> 01:17:17.853
So, you two have known each
other for a long time.

01:17:19.689 --> 01:17:21.690
Seems like an eternity.

01:17:24.819 --> 01:17:26.111
Please don't bother, Alan.

01:17:26.196 --> 01:17:29.198
Every time you turn that thing on it
just gets printed out in my office.

01:17:29.282 --> 01:17:31.617
And yes, yes, yes,
yes, yes, yes, yes' yes,

01:17:31.701 --> 01:17:35.955
that includes your little computer
conversation with MacLeod the other day.

01:17:36.039 --> 01:17:39.375
Besides, what good could
you possibly do, old man?

01:17:39.459 --> 01:17:42.795
What do you mean?
Oh, I don't know.

01:17:43.713 --> 01:17:46.799
How about for starters that there simply
isn't enough energy on the planet...

01:17:46.883 --> 01:17:48.801
to take down the shield
without killing us all?

01:17:48.885 --> 01:17:52.137
If I'm going too fast, slow me down, but
I think you should know this all, Alan.

01:17:52.222 --> 01:17:54.098
I mean, you designed the thing.

01:17:54.182 --> 01:17:56.809
You and this... MacLeod.

01:17:56.893 --> 01:17:59.728
But that was only in case
the shield was threatened.

01:17:59.813 --> 01:18:01.814
[ Laughing ]

01:18:03.567 --> 01:18:05.401
Well, that's funny, Alan!

01:18:05.485 --> 01:18:09.154
'Cause I was under the impression that
that's precisely what had happened.

01:18:12.158 --> 01:18:14.326
But it really doesn't
matter now, does it?

01:18:18.748 --> 01:18:21.000
So why don't you and I try and relax.

01:18:21.751 --> 01:18:23.252
No tears.

01:18:24.254 --> 01:18:27.089
Because it's business as usual—

01:18:27.173 --> 01:18:28.674
forever.

01:18:28.758 --> 01:18:31.594
You have allowed yourself
to become a traitor, Alan.

01:18:31.678 --> 01:18:35.973
And as I think you know, we have
a fabulous place for traitors.

01:18:37.267 --> 01:18:39.226
Don't we?

01:18:43.773 --> 01:18:45.024
Gentlemen,

01:18:45.108 --> 01:18:50.696
I can now assure you that Cobalt
will no longer be a problem.

01:18:50.780 --> 01:18:52.364
In fact, earlier today...

01:18:52.449 --> 01:18:55.951
the Shield Police were once
again able to stop an attempt—

01:19:04.711 --> 01:19:06.211
Hi.

01:19:06.296 --> 01:19:08.672
Excuse me, but I do believe
that you'll find...

01:19:08.757 --> 01:19:11.550
the costume party is
in another building.

01:19:11.635 --> 01:19:13.218
This happens to be a meeting,

01:19:13.303 --> 01:19:16.555
[ Groans ] and no one interrupts
a meeting of the corporation.

01:19:16.640 --> 01:19:18.557
The corporation.
What luck.

01:19:18.642 --> 01:19:21.477
You see, I've come to
join the corporation.

01:19:22.479 --> 01:19:24.104
And here you all are.

01:19:24.189 --> 01:19:26.357
Oww.

01:19:26.441 --> 01:19:28.359
Where do I sign up?

01:19:28.443 --> 01:19:31.320
Oh, I think I've had enough of you.

01:19:31.404 --> 01:19:35.074
Good-bye, Attila.
[ Chuckles ]

01:19:35.158 --> 01:19:37.284
[ Gunshots ]

01:19:46.127 --> 01:19:47.670
Ah!

01:19:47.754 --> 01:19:50.089
[ Chuckling ]
Yes, indeed.

01:19:50.173 --> 01:19:51.799
That was brilliantly done.

01:19:52.592 --> 01:19:53.801
Bravo.

01:20:03.978 --> 01:20:05.437
Yes!

01:20:06.815 --> 01:20:08.691
You know, guys,

01:20:08.775 --> 01:20:12.695
this is no way to treat your
number one draft choice.

01:20:13.780 --> 01:20:15.322
Hey.

01:20:15.407 --> 01:20:18.450
[ Gasping ]

01:20:23.164 --> 01:20:25.582
[ Bones Cracking ]

01:20:49.315 --> 01:20:51.150
[ Grunts ]

01:21:06.499 --> 01:21:08.333
Partners.

01:21:08.418 --> 01:21:13.005
I believe you cannot run a
business without partners.

01:21:13.089 --> 01:21:14.506
Right.

01:21:14.591 --> 01:21:16.925
This is a business, isn't it?
Oh, yes, it is.

01:21:17.010 --> 01:21:18.510
Ah.

01:21:18.595 --> 01:21:21.513
We like to think of it
as a good business. Mmm.

01:21:22.932 --> 01:21:25.100
What exactly is it that you want...

01:21:26.936 --> 01:21:28.437
partner?

01:21:32.525 --> 01:21:34.860
The Highlander.

01:21:34.944 --> 01:21:36.445
Right.

01:21:36.529 --> 01:21:40.449
Wilson, could we get on the
Highlander thing as soon as possible?

01:21:42.327 --> 01:21:45.370
[ Electrical Pulses ]

01:21:55.965 --> 01:21:57.466
MacLeod.

01:22:04.307 --> 01:22:06.809
You created that monstrosity?

01:22:07.727 --> 01:22:09.645
Why?

01:22:09.729 --> 01:22:11.814
It was necessary at the time.

01:22:12.982 --> 01:22:14.399
[ Scoffs ]

01:22:14.484 --> 01:22:17.778
So was Noah's flood, but that
at least served its purpose.

01:22:17.862 --> 01:22:21.657
Cleansed the Earth from evil
and gave it a fresh start.

01:22:21.741 --> 01:22:24.159
Thirty-three degrees,

01:22:25.328 --> 01:22:28.705
26 minutes north latitude.

01:22:28.790 --> 01:22:31.917
That's where Neyman said
there was a system failure.

01:22:32.001 --> 01:22:36.129
Meaning what?
Meaning we can go above the shield.

01:22:36.214 --> 01:22:39.424
We will still require a
longitude, won't we?

01:22:39.509 --> 01:22:42.094
MacLeod.

01:22:42.178 --> 01:22:44.137
Alan Neyman's been taken to Max.

01:22:44.222 --> 01:22:46.431
Max? Who's Max?

01:22:46.516 --> 01:22:49.017
A high-security prison.

01:22:50.270 --> 01:22:52.563
MacLeod.

01:22:53.857 --> 01:22:56.692
Your time is now!

01:22:56.776 --> 01:22:59.611
[ Electrical Pulses ]

01:23:03.908 --> 01:23:06.368
[ Woman's Voice On Intercom ]
You have entered a restricted area.

01:23:06.452 --> 01:23:08.579
Please identify yourself immediately.

01:23:08.663 --> 01:23:11.957
I am Juan Sánchez Villa-Lobos Ramirez,

01:23:12.041 --> 01:23:16.503
chief metallurgist to King Philip II
of Spain, and I am at your service.

01:23:16.588 --> 01:23:20.173
This is Checkpoint One outside
of security installation Max.

01:23:20.258 --> 01:23:22.885
Identify yourselves.
Hey, take it easy, man.

01:23:22.969 --> 01:23:26.972
First time in the desert.
Which way to Vegas?

01:23:27.056 --> 01:23:29.516
Okay, jerk-face.
Stay put, and we'll come get you.

01:23:32.478 --> 01:23:34.646
Hit it, dude!
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:23:34.731 --> 01:23:36.523
[ Man ] ♪ Rockin' ♪

01:23:38.943 --> 01:23:40.277
♪ Rollin' through ♪

01:23:40.361 --> 01:23:43.238
♪ And here we go ♪

01:23:46.075 --> 01:23:48.577
Get ready. Here it comes.

01:23:50.079 --> 01:23:53.373
♪♪ [ Continues, Indistinct ]

01:24:41.381 --> 01:24:42.714
Hi.

01:24:42.799 --> 01:24:45.133
You won't shoot me, will you?
I mean—

01:24:46.636 --> 01:24:49.012
Oh, thank you.

01:24:49.097 --> 01:24:51.473
I was just hitching a ride...

01:24:51.557 --> 01:24:53.725
and then these two
guys grabbed me and—

01:24:53.810 --> 01:24:57.813
Oh, my.
And threw me in the trunk and—

01:24:57.897 --> 01:24:59.231
Oh, shit.

01:25:12.286 --> 01:25:15.914
Hello. I'm Dr. Sonny Jackson, and
I've looked over your report.

01:25:15.999 --> 01:25:18.333
As near as I can tell, you have
a few bruises and lacerations,

01:25:18.418 --> 01:25:20.460
but I think you'll be
okay in a day or so.

01:25:20.545 --> 01:25:22.587
Thanks. How about them?

01:25:22.672 --> 01:25:25.007
No way. They were both dead
before the car stopped.

01:25:25.091 --> 01:25:27.259
I'm amazed they got
as far as they did.

01:25:27.343 --> 01:25:29.219
Gosh, I've never seen
a mess like that.

01:25:29.303 --> 01:25:31.722
They must have taken about
a hundred bullets or so.

01:25:31.806 --> 01:25:33.515
Excuse me. 108.

01:25:33.599 --> 01:25:35.100
112, myself.

01:25:35.184 --> 01:25:38.186
Come on. You're not counting
that little scratch, are you?

01:25:38.271 --> 01:25:41.773
Scratch? What are you talking about?
It passed right through me.

01:25:42.817 --> 01:25:44.776
[ Ramirez ] And just look
at my splendid waistcoat.

01:25:45.653 --> 01:25:47.112
[ Both Groan ]

01:25:48.197 --> 01:25:50.866
Wait a minute.
You guys-- You boys are—

01:25:50.950 --> 01:25:53.535
You guys are... de-- Wh—

01:25:53.619 --> 01:25:54.703
Larry!

01:26:32.408 --> 01:26:34.743
All right, these tunnels run
along both sides of Max...

01:26:34.827 --> 01:26:36.578
and they end up at the same place.

01:26:36.662 --> 01:26:39.081
They both have security rooms,
and Neyman's in one of them.

01:26:39.165 --> 01:26:41.500
So we should split up, and we'll
meet back together at the end.

01:26:41.584 --> 01:26:43.168
You take this way.
Let's go, MacLeod.

01:27:24.919 --> 01:27:27.045
No more. No more!
No more!

01:27:27.130 --> 01:27:28.713
Alan.

01:27:29.465 --> 01:27:31.466
Oh, my God.

01:27:31.551 --> 01:27:34.094
[ Groans ]
Please.

01:27:34.971 --> 01:27:38.390
Listen. Other coordinate—

01:27:38.474 --> 01:27:41.726
Six degrees, 42 minutes west.

01:27:41.811 --> 01:27:44.187
You can get through the shield there.

01:27:44.272 --> 01:27:46.815
You must see for yourself.

01:27:47.817 --> 01:27:49.568
Mac?
Yes?

01:27:51.362 --> 01:27:53.280
We did the right thing to build it.

01:27:55.324 --> 01:27:56.950
Yes, we did.

01:28:04.876 --> 01:28:07.752
[ MacLeod ] I won't forget you.
[ Louise ] MacLeod.

01:28:07.837 --> 01:28:09.671
[ Katana ]
How very touching.

01:28:09.755 --> 01:28:14.009
You don't have to worry.
No one gets out of Max.

01:28:14.093 --> 01:28:16.678
But you said nobody
would get in either.

01:28:18.890 --> 01:28:20.849
Who's that?

01:28:20.933 --> 01:28:23.810
Louise Marcus.
The head of Cobalt.

01:28:23.895 --> 01:28:27.147
A powerful enemy, I'm sure.

01:28:27.231 --> 01:28:29.191
It doesn't matter now,

01:28:29.275 --> 01:28:31.902
because they're both dead.

01:28:37.116 --> 01:28:39.284
Don't let the door close!

01:28:54.926 --> 01:28:56.968
Holy shit!

01:29:19.784 --> 01:29:22.285
-Just stay back!
- I can help!

01:29:22.370 --> 01:29:24.663
No, you can't— not this time!

01:29:34.548 --> 01:29:35.715
[ Shouts ]

01:29:44.016 --> 01:29:46.559
Most people have a full measure of life.

01:29:48.229 --> 01:29:52.023
And most people just watch
it slowly drip away.

01:29:58.489 --> 01:30:01.157
But if you can summon it all up...

01:30:02.743 --> 01:30:04.703
at one time,

01:30:06.455 --> 01:30:08.665
in one place,

01:30:08.749 --> 01:30:10.417
[ Whimpers ]

01:30:12.795 --> 01:30:16.131
you can accomplish something...

01:30:16.215 --> 01:30:18.550
glorious!

01:30:34.317 --> 01:30:39.321
My time here is over.
You must go and search out Katana.

01:30:39.405 --> 01:30:42.157
It'll take the power of you
both to destroy the shield.

01:30:42.241 --> 01:30:44.200
Will I ever see you again?

01:30:44.285 --> 01:30:48.121
Who knows, Highlander?
Who knows?

01:30:49.874 --> 01:30:51.458
Go.

01:31:18.152 --> 01:31:19.486
Show time.

01:31:27.453 --> 01:31:28.953
Come on.

01:31:40.383 --> 01:31:42.300
Outstanding!

01:31:52.144 --> 01:31:53.770
[ Exhales ]

01:32:08.494 --> 01:32:10.620
Time for your bitch to die!

01:32:10.704 --> 01:32:12.997
Whatever happens, don't stop.

01:32:13.082 --> 01:32:14.541
What?

01:32:18.045 --> 01:32:20.171
[ Yells, Grunts ]

01:32:25.469 --> 01:32:28.471
[ Grunting Continues ]

01:32:47.741 --> 01:32:49.075
MacLeod!

01:32:53.998 --> 01:32:55.707
[ Screams ]

01:32:59.587 --> 01:33:02.464
[ Screaming, Whimpering ]

01:33:24.528 --> 01:33:26.070
No!

01:33:33.329 --> 01:33:35.413
[ Laughing ]

01:33:41.754 --> 01:33:44.088
I'm fine. I'm fine!

01:33:52.264 --> 01:33:54.182
Oh, great.

01:33:57.019 --> 01:34:00.522
[ Electricity Pulsing, Crackling ]

01:34:22.962 --> 01:34:24.629
Let's go.

01:34:39.979 --> 01:34:41.604
[ Louise Grunting ]

01:34:46.151 --> 01:34:48.778
MacLeod! MacLeod!

01:34:48.862 --> 01:34:50.655
Hold on!

01:34:50.739 --> 01:34:53.658
That's it! Come on!

01:35:21.353 --> 01:35:24.439
Life is going to be quite
predictable without MacLeod.

01:35:28.110 --> 01:35:29.777
[ Glass Ball Shatters ]

01:35:31.280 --> 01:35:36.200
Aren't we getting just a
little overconfident, partner?

01:35:37.202 --> 01:35:38.745
You are betting on me, aren't you?

01:35:38.829 --> 01:35:40.622
Oh, yes.

01:35:41.624 --> 01:35:43.958
You see, I always play the favorite.

01:35:45.252 --> 01:35:47.295
[ Explosion ]

01:35:47.379 --> 01:35:49.922
[ Electrical Pulsing Crackling Continues ]

01:35:52.426 --> 01:35:54.927
[ Wind Blowing ]

01:36:49.108 --> 01:36:51.067
Alan was right.

